---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import Layout from '../../../components/layout/Layout.astro';
import ArtworkSchema from '../../../components/seo/ArtworkSchema.astro';

const lang = 'en' as const;
const title = 'En el fertil suelo';

const img1 = (await import('../../../assets/images/obras/fertil-suelo/fertil-suelo-01.webp')).default;
const img2 = (await import('../../../assets/images/obras/fertil-suelo/fertil-suelo-02.webp')).default;
---

<Layout
  lang={lang}
  title="En el fertil suelo — Work"
  description="En el fertil suelo (2017). Video (3'15''). A hand uncovers, beneath the sand, a text from Canto III of the Iliad. X Premio Luis Caballero nomination. Maria Elvira Escallon."
  ogImage={img1.src}
>


  <ArtworkSchema
    title="En el fertil suelo"
    year="2017–2018"
    medium="Video, sculpture"
    description="Video in which a hand slowly uncovers, beneath layers of sand, a text from Canto III of the Iliad, while another hand covers it again. An echo of the longing for peace after the signing of the Peace Process in Colombia."
    url="https://mariaelviraescallon.org/en/works/en-el-fertil-suelo/"
  />

  <article class="work-page">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="work-page__header">
        <p class="label">Work / 008</p>
        <h1>{title}</h1>
        <p class="work-page__meta">2017–2018 &nbsp;/&nbsp; Video, sculpture &nbsp;/&nbsp; Variable dimensions</p>
      </header>

      <!-- Main gallery -->
      <div class="work-page__gallery">
        <Image src={img1} alt="En el fertil suelo — General view of the sculptural installation" loading="eager" fetchpriority="high" widths={[480, 900, 1400]} sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 1200px" />
        <Image src={img2} alt="En el fertil suelo — Detail of the sculptural figures" loading="lazy" widths={[480, 900, 1400]} sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 1200px" />
      </div>

      <!-- Text + Technical sheet -->
      <div class="work-page__body">
        <div class="work-page__text">

          <p class="curatorial">
            "En el fertil suelo" relates to the political moment we were living in Colombia in the years following the signing of the Peace Process.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            In the video, a hand slowly uncovers a text that lies beneath many layers of sand. When it is about to reach its goal and we manage to read some of the inscription that was covered, the other hand covers the text again, putting sand back on top. In this way, the first hand must restart its task, in a process that seems to have no end.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The text of the inscription is part of Canto III of the Iliad, which describes a moment during the Trojan War in which its leaders decide to stop that bloody war. Then, while on the battlefield, the armies disarm. The warriors step down from the war chariots, remove their armor, and stand there, exposed, very close to one another. It is a moment of tense calm, of extreme vulnerability and, at the same time, of great hope for Achaeans and Trojans, historical enemies for decades. I associate that episode with the moment we lived after the signing of the peace process.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            This project sought to echo the profound longing for peace that so many of us felt in Colombia.
          </p>

        </div>

        <aside class="work-page__ficha">
          <h4>TECHNICAL SHEET</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            <strong>En el fertil suelo</strong><br>
            2017–2018<br><br>
            Video, sculpture.<br>
            Light and sound installations.<br>
            Variable dimensions
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">AWARDS</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            X Premio Luis Caballero nomination<br>
            IDARTES, 2018
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">EXHIBITIONS</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            MAMBO, Bogota, 2019<br>
            X Premio Luis Caballero — Galeria Santa Fe, Bogota, 2018
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">LOCATION</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            Galeria Santa Fe, Bogota (X Premio Luis Caballero)<br>
            MAMBO, Bogota, 2019
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">HOW TO CITE</h4>
          <div class="ficha" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">
            Escallon, M.E. (2017–2018). “En el fertil suelo”.
            Video, sculpture. Available at:
            mariaelviraescallon.org/en/works/en-el-fertil-suelo/
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>

    </div>
  </article>

</Layout>

<style>
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    }
</style>
